{
  "stem": "15393.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Her father was truly a sort of one of those holy men, who-- who-- who just sit in the synagogue and pray.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that's what he did, all his life, just prayed.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And when we came for Passover, [LAUGHS] it was-- the seder night was non-ending.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It was an absolutely-- maybe that's how it should be.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Or-- I know-- I know seder nights in Israel are quite different.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But to me, it was, again, a shock to my system, when I, years and years later, went to-- to an Israeli Seder.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I thought-- I thought, I don't think that is right.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "This is not the right sort of seder, because I was so accustomed to the way my grandfather.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "You know, [HEBREW] which means-- you know what it means.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I mean, semi-reclining and-- and taking every word, you know, chanting every word from the Haggadah.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "That was, you know.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So on one hand, I had this.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And my mother came from this background.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But my father was very assimilated.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "He-- absolutely nothing religious for him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So I was brought up in this vein.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I-- every Friday, my grandmother would send parcels, which would arrive every Friday.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "She would bake all sorts of lovely things for Shabbat-- and-- or for her, for Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And-- and that arrived, religiously, every-- every Friday, to have it on the table, a challah, which she made herself, and all that.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "When I think about it, today, it's almost unheard of that-- that one can do it, that one can send it by post, and it arrives fresh.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] It's-- it's unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But she-- she used to do every Friday.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And my mother, on the other hand, used to write a letter in Yiddish to her parents, so that they get it for Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
